1. Create Maven project
2. In pom.xml, add dependencies
3. Create Folder "Response_Files" under the project
4. Create below folder structure
src/main/java -> create one package i.e api_request_classes
src/test/java -> create two packages that are resources, utilities and testcases
5. Inside utilities package create 5 java classes -> BaseClass, AuthUtils, ConfigReader, ExcelReader and Helper
6. Inside resources package create two files -> config.properties and Test_Data.xlsx
7. Write code in ConfigReader and ExcelReader java class
8. Write code in BaseClass
9. Create 5 java classes in testcases package (Create_API, GET_API, Update_API, Delete_API, Main_Testcases_Flow)
and write the code. Here I have used pathParameter as well
10. To not hard code the request body and to pass the value for each field at runtime, we use Lombok library
11. Add Lombok dependency in pom.xml
12. Inside src/test/java create one package "api_request_classes" which will have the java classes for each if the request APIs
13. Create one java class CreateAPI_Request inside package "api_request_classes"
14. This class will have all the fields from input json. Using Lombok annotations will automatically generate code
like getters, setters, constructors etc.
15. Create a java class "CreateAPI_POJO" and call method of this class in Main_Testcase_Flow java class